The implements Keyword

The `implements` keyword allows a class to enforce that it conforms to a specific interface.

### Basic Usage

```typescript
interface Printable {
  print(): void;
}

interface Serializable {
  toJSON(): string;
}

class Report implements Printable, Serializable {
  print(): void {
    console.log("Printing report...");
  }

  toJSON(): string {
    return JSON.stringify({ report: "data" });
  }
}
```

### Multiple Interfaces

```typescript
interface Identifiable {
  id: number;
}

interface Named {
  name: string;
}

class Entity implements Identifiable, Named {
  constructor(
    public id: number,
    public name: string
  ) {}
}
```

### implements vs extends

| Aspect | implements | extends |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Purpose | Contract enforcement | Code reuse |
| Source | Interface(s) | Class |
| Implementation | Must implement all | Inherits implementation |
| Count | Multiple | Single |

### Class Type Checking

```typescript
interface Checkable {
  check(name: string): boolean;
}

class NameChecker implements Checkable {
  check(name: string): boolean {
    return name.length > 0;
  }
  // Implicitly implements Checkable
}
```

### Optional Members in Implements

```typescript
interface Config {
  host: string;
  port?: number;
}

class ServerConfig implements Config {
  host: string;
  // port is optional, can be omitted
  constructor(host: string) {
    this.host = host;
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** `implements` is a pure type-level check. It does not affect runtime behavior.

codeExample:
interface Drawable {
  draw(context: CanvasRenderingContext2D): void;
}

interface Resizable {
  resize(scale: number): void;
}

interface Movable {
  move(dx: number, dy: number): void;
}

class Shape implements Drawable, Resizable, Movable {
  constructor(
    public x: number,
    public y: number,
    public size: number
  ) {}

  draw(ctx: CanvasRenderingContext2D): void {
    // Drawing logic
  }

  resize(scale: number): void {
    this.size *= scale;
  }

  move(dx: number, dy: number): void {
    this.x += dx;
    this.y += dy;
  }
}
